ROYAL DUTCH MOVES HIGHER AT MIDDAY . Shares in Royal Dutch built on early light gains by midday on Monday , trading 3 . 20 guilders up at 285 . 40 amid a generally weaker Amsterdam bourse after weekend reports it was planning a bid for British Gas . The companies declined to comment on the report in Britain ' s Sunday Telegraph which said the Anglo - Dutch oil giant had approached British Gas with plans for a 40 billion stg merger . But dealers in Amsterdam on Monday remained sceptical . " People are treating it strictly as a rumour but there is some buying coming into the stock - - that could be originating from London , " one said . - - Amsterdam newsroom + 31 20 504 5000 
